    "causal_summary": "Two parallel code skills (sk-code-web and sk-code-full-stack) overlap in phase model and intent vocabulary, causing advisor routing ambiguity (0.87 vs 0.86 tie). This packet creates a new umbrella skill `sk-code` with stack-detection-first smart routing — web stack live (carried verbatim from sk-code-web), non-web stacks (React/Node/Go/Swift/React-Native) scaffolded as empty templated stubs pointing back to sk-code-full-stack for canonical content. Legacy skills preserved on disk untouched per user directive 'I dont want you to overwrite the 2 skills' — deprecation enforced via additive frontmatter keys plus a code-level DEPRECATED_SKILLS exclusion list in skill_advisor.py and explicit.ts that survives doctor:skill-advisor :confirm rebuilds. ~40 active cross-repo references retargeted across 7 tiers (advisor scoring, graph metadata, sister SKILL.md cross-refs, root instruction files, agent definitions, READMEs, deprecation markers); ~268 archival references in specs/, .opencode/changelog/, observability/ remain untouched. Five ADRs document routing ordering (stack-first), naming (bare sk-code), placeholder strategy (templated stubs), deprecation strategy (exclusion list), and universal/ namespace scoping (tight, no browser-coupled content).",
